iwork.eheap2
Interface FieldValueTypes

All Known Implementing Classes:
EventHeap, Field, FieldValue, SecureEventHeap, Tuple
public interface FieldValueTypes

This is an interface that contains members with the enumerations for valid value types for the post and template value sub-fields of event fields.

Field Detail

ACTUAL

public static final int ACTUAL
Returned by getPostValueType() and getTemplateValueType() if the sub-field value contains an actual object for its value. May not be passed field creation/modification methods for post value and template value-- a Serializable object should be passed to the appropriate equivalent method instead.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

FORMAL

public static final int FORMAL
Pass as int value to field creation/modification methods for post value and template value. This value indicates that the particular sub-field value is formal (in other words matches any value as long as field name and type are the same. Also returned by getPostValueType() and getTemplateValueType() methods.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

VIRTUAL

public static final int VIRTUAL
Pass as int value to field creation/modification methods for post value and template value. This value indicates that the particular sub-field value is virtual (in other words ignored in all matching). Also returned by getPostValueType() and getTemplateValueType() methods.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

AUTOSET

public static final int AUTOSET
Returned by getPostValueType() and getTemplateValueType() if the sub-field value is automatically set by the Event Heap. This value may not be overridden. May not be passed field creation/modification methods for post value and template value-- this value may only be set internally by the Event Heap.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

AUTOSET_OVERRIDEABLE

public static final int AUTOSET_OVERRIDEABLE
Returned by getPostValueType() and getTemplateValueType() if the sub-field value is automatically set by the Event Heap and is overrideable. May not be passed field creation/modification methods for post value and template value-- this value may only be set internally by the Event Heap. Note that even if the value is not overridden, the Event Heap will only set this value the first time the event is posted or used as a template (in other words, the Event Heap client effectively overrides itself the first time). After that the value will stay the same even if the value to which the field would currently be automatically set is different than the orginal value to which the field was set.

See Also:
Constant Field Values
